xml:lang="ps"><lang/><w>kas-, kəs%i:%i katəl</w><gloss><q>смотреть</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgy"><lang/><w>kas-</w><gloss><q>смотреть</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sgy"><w/><gloss><q>видеть</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="yah"><lang/><w>ḱas-</w><gloss><q>смотреть</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"><lang/><w>čas-, čes-, čis-</w></mentioned> (<bibl corresp="#ref_Sköld._Pam."><biblScope>178, 182</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="sog-x-chr"><lang/><w>pcqs-</w><gloss><q>ждать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*kas(ks-)</w><gloss><q>наблюдатель</q></gloss></mentioned>, в %i'nγrks%i ‘астролог’, „наблюдатель звезд“, <mentioned xml:lang="zkh"><lang/><w>škaš-</w><gloss><q>смотреть</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>kas-</w><gloss><q>являться</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>kas(ākas-)</w><gloss><q>смотреть</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>kāś-</w><gloss><q>сиять</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>смотреть</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Может быть, скифское имя %iΚάσαγος%i = ос. %ikæsæg%i ‘смотрящий’. — От этого же корня — <xr><ref target="#entry_cæst"/></xr> ‘глаз’. См. также <xr><ref target="#entry_fælgæsyn"/></xr> (←%i*pari-kas-%i) ‘смотреть’, <xr><ref target="#entry_ængas"/></xr> ‘взгляд’, <xr><ref target="#entry_ængæs"/></xr> ‘подобный’ (← %i*han-kasa-%i).%n<bibl corresp="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"><biblScope>II 46</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl corresp="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."><biblScope>57</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl corresp="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."><biblScope>44</biblScope></bibl>.— <bibl corresp="#ref_ОЯФ_I"><biblScope>24, 171</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">It is of Iranian origin as some other generally used verbs. Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="fa-x-dial"><lang/><w>bi-kes- %i:%i bi-kas-</w><gloss><q>to look</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl corresp="#ref_Жуковский"><biblScope>I 202</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/><w>nikās dār-</w><gloss><q>to oversee</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>nigāh</w><gloss><q>look</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/><w>kas-, kəs%i:%i katəl</w><gloss><q>to look</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgy"><lang/><w>kas-</w><gloss><q>to look</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sgy"><w/><gloss><q>to see</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="yah"><lang/><w>ḱas-</w><gloss><q>to look</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"><lang/><w>čas-, čes-, čis-</w></mentioned> (<bibl corresp="#ref_Sköld._Pam."><biblScope>178, 182</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="sog-x-chr"><lang/><w>pcqs-</w><gloss><q>to wait</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*kas(ks-)</w><gloss><q>observer</q></gloss></mentioned>, in %i'nγrks%i ‘astrologer’, „star observer“, <mentioned xml:lang="zkh"><lang/><w>škaš-</w><gloss><q>to look</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>kas-</w><gloss><q>to appear</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>kas(ākas-)</w><gloss><q>to look</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>kāś-</w><gloss><q>to shine</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>to look</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Maybe the Scythian name %iΚάσαγος%i = Ossetic %ikæsæg%i ‘looking’. — The following words is from this root as well: <xr><ref target="#entry_cæst"/></xr> ‘eye’. See also <xr><ref target="#entry_fælgæsyn"/></xr> (←%i*pari-kas-%i) ‘to look’, <xr><ref target="#entry_ængas"/></xr> ‘look’, <xr><ref target="#entry_ængæs"/></xr> ‘similar’ (← %i*han-kasa-%i).%n<bibl corresp="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"><biblScope>II 46</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl corresp="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."><biblScope>57</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl corresp="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."><biblScope>44</biblScope></bibl>.— <bibl corresp="#ref_ОЯФ_I"><biblScope>24, 171</biblScope></bibl>